MongoDB files for
Yahoo! Cloud System Benchmark (YCSB)
====================================

Links
-----
http://wiki.github.com/10gen-labs/YCSB/


http://wiki.github.com/brianfrankcooper/YCSB/
http://research.yahoo.com/Web_Information_Management/YCSB


Getting Started
---------------

1. Download the latest release of YCSB:

    wget https://github.com/downloads/brianfrankcooper/YCSB/ycsb-0.1.4.tar.gz
    tar xfvz ycsb-0.1.4
    cd ycsb-0.1.4

2. Set up a database to benchmark. There is a README file under each binding
   directory.

2a. See file mongodb/README.md for MongoDB related instructions

3. Run YCSB command. 

    bin/ycsb load mongodb -P workloads/workloada
    bin/ycsb run mongodb -P workloads/workloada

   Running the `ycsb` command without any argument will print the usage. 
   
   See https://github.com/brianfrankcooper/YCSB/wiki/Running-a-Workload
   for a detailed documentation on how to run a workload 
   and https://github.com/10gen-labs/YCSB/wiki/Running-YCSB-on-MongoDB
   for a detailed documentation on how to run YCSB on MongoDB

   See https://github.com/brianfrankcooper/YCSB/wiki/Core-Properties for 
   the list of available workload properties.
   and https://github.com/10gen-labs/YCSB/wiki for
   additional and changed MongoDB properties
   
